'''Osada Nimasu Amateru-Mitama Shrine''' (おさだにますあまてるみたまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Sakurai|Q127026|WD=Q127026|1=Sakurai, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|lt=shikinaisha great shrine|Q134917288|WD=Q134917288|1=Shikinai Taisha}}, and its former {{ill|lt=shrine rank|Q10444029|WD=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} was {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== History ===
=== Outline ===
This place is said to have once been the site of Osata-no-Sakitama-no-miya, a palace of {{ill|lt=Emperor Bidatsu|Q316637|WD=Q316637|1=Emperor Bidatsu}}, and the shrine is said to mark where the {{ill|lt=Himatsuri-be|Q109597716|WD=Q109597716|lt=Hinomatsuri-be|1=Hinomatsuri-be}} established by Bidatsu was placed (though there is also a theory that Osata-no-Sakitama-no-miya was at {{ill|lt=Kasuga Shrine (Sakurai)|UNKNOWN|lt=Kasuga Shrine}} in Kaijū, Sakurai). In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} it was listed as a great shrine, but afterward it disappears from historical records; in the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963|1=Edo period}} it called itself Kasuga Shrine.

=== Court rank ===
*{{ill|lt=Ten'an (Japan)|Q1075611|WD=Q1075611|lt=Ten'an|1=Ten'an}} 3 ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|WD=Q23897|1=859}}), {{ill|lt=January 27|Q2284|WD=Q2284|1=January 27}}: promoted from Junior Fifth Lower to Junior Fifth Upper (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|WD=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}'') - written as “Osada Amateru-Mitama-no-Kami”

=== Enshrined deity ===
'''Amateru-Mitama-no-Mikoto'''<br />There are various theories on the deity’s identity.
* ''Jingi Hōten'': aramitama of Amaterasu Ōmikami
* ''{{ill|lt=Jinja Kakuroku|Q11590708|WD=Q11590708|1=Jinja Kakuroku}}'': Ama-no-hi-no-kami-no-Mikoto
* ''{{ill|lt=Jinmyōchō Kōshō|Q11588824|WD=Q11588824|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō Studies}}'': Amateru-kuni-teru-hiko-hoakari-no-Mikoto / Nigihayahi-no-Mikoto, ancestor of the Shiki clan
* ''{{ill|lt=Tokusen Jinmyōchō|Q11571092|WD=Q11571092|1=Tokusen Jinmyōchō}}'': {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Hoakari-no-Mikoto|Q10940411|WD=Q10940411|1=Amenohoakari}}

